                <p class="aboutme">This project is meant to be an interactive narrative experience modeled after horror ARG sites.<br><br>
                The entire site is written with a combination of HTML, CSS, and Javascript, without using outside components. In terms of design, it is meant to look like a normal corporate website for a large-scale bakery.<br><br>
                However, sinister clues hinting at a different purpose behind the bakery are hiding in various spots throughout the site.<br><br>
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li><em>Animated rolling pies hide distorted images, cryptic videos, and threatening messages.</em></li>
                    <li><em>An alert in the error page hides messages from a mysterious person looking for answers.</em></li>
                    <li><em>A secret code hidden in the text contains the password to an employee-only page.</em></li>
                    <li><em>Ordering a certain type and amount of baked goods in the order form will send a sinister confirmation email.</em></li>
                </ul><br><br>
                <p class="aboutme">
                The project not only is an experiment in storytelling through website design and functionality, but it also practices skills in regards to Express, EJS, HTML/CSS, Prisma, password-protected content, and forms.
